n module. Circularly polarized UV can induce up to ~4% optical purity in alanine films, and calcite/quartz adsorption may contribute modest bias, though amplification is necessary (Parker et al., 2011; Meierhenrich et al., 2015; Hazen et al., 2001; Asthagiri & Hazen, 2007)."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Hydrothermal pyruvate to alanine via mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxides", "description": "Direct warm alkaline vent route where hydrothermal pyruvate is converted to alanine with high selectivity on mixed Fe(II)/Fe(III) oxyhydroxide precipitates.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_011", "rxn_016"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Native nickel mild aqueous pyruvate reductive amination", "description": "Pyruvate formed hydrothermally is aminated to alanine at room temperature with H2 over Ni surfaces, then L-selection is applied.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_012", "rxn_016"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Vent sulfide mineral pyruvate route", "description": "Pyruvate enters a mineral-pruned hydrothermal reaction landscape where sulfide phases permit alanine formation under vent-gas conditions.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_013", "rxn_016"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Serpentinization-like pyridoxal shuttle route", "description": "Pyridoxal is first aminated to pyridoxamine on Ni0, then transfers amino functionality to pyruvate to produce alanine before chiral enrichment.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_014", "rxn_015", "rxn_016"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_015", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Acetaldehyde Strecker route from hydrothermal carbon", "description": "Reduced hydrothermal carbon passes through formate and acetate to acetaldehyde, which undergoes Strecker synthesis to alanine aminonitrile and hydrolysis to alanine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", 